RC 54166.
##

Ambling into History: The Unlikely Odyssey of George W.
Bush.
RC 54167.
by Frank Bruni.
read by Richard Hauenstein.
2 cassettes.
Journalist examines Bush's personal characteristics and
qualities during his progress from Texas governor to United
States president and recounts anecdotes from campaign
coverage. Describes Bush's reactions to the terrorist attack
on September 11, 2001, that changed the tenor of his
presidency. Bestseller 2002.
RC 54167.
##

The Age of Homespun: Objects and Stories in the Creation of
an American Myth.
